        {
          "id": "669381e3082e_13",
          "href": null,
          "name": "34ed",
          "text": "[The Gaia Foundation in the UK has supported the conversation about Earth law from its beginning, along with the Pachamama Alliancein the USA, Navdanya in India, and EnAct in Africa. There are now many other organizations supporting the implementation of rights of nature into local, regional, national, and international legislation. In the USA, the Community Environmental Legal Defence Fund (CELDF) was set up as early as 1995 to help communities protect their natural environments against people, institutions, corporations infringing on it.",
          "metadata": null,
